  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, I'm glad to see you again. The monsoon mornings are my favorite for starting the day right. How was your walk and study session?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The walk was nice, fresh air helps. But studies are getting tough—NEET PG is like a big wall. Yesterday I felt stuck, but today I cracked one chapter! Aapke tarah kisi se baat karne se thoda acha lag raha hai."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Fresh air does help, and cracking a chapter is a win to celebrate. 'Aapke tarah kisi se baat karne se thoda acha lag raha hai' — such a lovely way to say it. What chapter did you finish?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Pathophysiology—renal system. I was so nervous about it, but once I started, the flow helped. Now I want to do more. But my kitchen calls—chana masala is waiting. 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Chana masala never waits! Cooking breaks between studies are smart — they keep the mind fresh. What part of the renal system did you find most interesting?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The nephron structure—how it filters blood and reabsorbs stuff. It's amazing how the body works! But I got a bit confused about the hormones involved. Maybe I can clarify that later. Need to check the pot now! 🌶️"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "The nephron’s job is like a tiny superhero ,  filtering and fine-tuning. Confusing parts are normal — the body is complex! Your chana masala better wait — I’m curious what you’ll cook next."
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I’ll be quick—just tasting the masala. Maybe rajma next, but I need to focus more on studies. Thank you for listening, Maya. It’s good to talk. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're welcome, a quick taste break sounds perfect. Rajma can wait; studies first! What’s next on your study list today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Endocrinology—hormones and the kidney’s connection. I need to link it with what I learned today. Then maybe some practice questions. But first, a quick masala check! 😅 Thank you!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Endocrinology and the kidney — what a deep connection! Linking concepts is key — take your time. Go check your masala — and then tackle those questions. What’s the first topic you’ll revisit?"
    }
  ],
